                <h3 class="subheading">Škoda Kylaq</h3>
               
                <ul>
                    <li>Revealed in November 2024 and entering production at Škoda's Pune plant in December 2024</li>
                    <li>Škoda's first sub-4-metre SUV in India</li>
                    <li>Built on MQB-A0-IN platform for local manufacturing</li>
                    <li>Positioned as an affordable sub-4m SUV with European-tech</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Exterior Styling & Road Presence</h2>

                <h3 class="subheading">Tata Nexon</h3>
               
                <p>Presents a bold, rugged identity with:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Dual-tone roof options</li>
                    <li>Diamond-cut alloys</li>
                    <li>Flared wheel arches</li>
                    <li>Refreshed grille/headlamp setup in facelift</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Škoda Kylaq</h3>
              
                <p>Embraces modernity with:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Crystalline LED head and tail lights</li>
                    <li>Gloss-black grille</li>
                    <li>Flush roof rails</li>
                    <li>17-inch alloys</li>
                    <li>Skid plates</li>
                </ul>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub Verdict:</span> Choose the <strong>Nexon</strong> for a tough, road-conquering look; opt for the <strong>Kylaq</strong> if you want understated elegance with premium cues.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Powertrains & Driveability</h2>

