                    <li>Wider selection of drivetrains (diesel, petrol, EV)</li>
                    <li>Rugged SUV looks with strong road presence</li>
                    <li>Better ground clearance for uneven terrain</li>
                    <li>Trusted after-sales across smaller towns</li>
                </ul>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">✅ Choose Škoda Kylaq if you value...</span></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Premium interior, ambient lighting, clever storage</li>
                    <li>Refined turbo-petrol performance in an automatic</li>
                    <li>Compact but roomy cabin with thoughtful ergonomics</li>
                    <li>European badge and evolving tech</li>
                </ul>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">BikeCarHub Final Verdict:</span></p>
                <p>Both offer compelling packages backed by top-tier safety. The <strong>Nexon</strong> is a pragmatic, feature-rich powerhouse with option diversity, while the <strong>Kylaq</strong> shines with refinement, design and petrol efficiency. If you crave EV or diesel flexibility and rugged flair, opt for the Nexon. If touring city roads in style with turbo-smooth comfort is your priority, the Kylaq is your answer.</p>

